The paper deals with the restricted isometry property (RIP) and efficient computation of matrices, which are topics commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Hadamard and Fourier transforms suggests a connection to signal processing (cs.SP), while the focus on computational efficiency suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the use of orthonormal matrices and sparsity suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS).
